What is the Terraform lifecycle?

4 Stages of Terraform Lifecycle:

Write Code  →  Init  →  Plan  →  Apply  →  Destroy

Stage by Stage:
1. terraform init

terraform init
# Downloads providers (AWS, Azure)
# Sets up backend (S3, local)
# First command always!

2. terraform plan

terraform plan
# Compares: current state vs desired code
# Shows what will be created/changed/destroyed
# Nothing actually happens — just preview

3. terraform apply

terraform apply
# Actually creates/modifies infrastructure
# Updates terraform.tfstate file

4. terraform destroy

terraform destroy
# Destroys all resources managed by terraform
# Updates state file

Lifecycle Meta-Arguments (important for interviews):

resource "aws_instance" "web" {
  ami           = "ami-12345"
  instance_type = "t3.micro"

  lifecycle {
    create_before_destroy = true   # create new before deleting old
    prevent_destroy       = true   # block accidental destroy
    ignore_changes        = [tags] # ignore tag changes
  }
}
